The governor-elect of Osun State, Senator Ademola Adeleke, yesterday, constituted a 37-member transition committee to facilitate a smooth transition between the incumbent and the newly-elected administration in the state. A statement by the Media Officer of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state, Oladele Bamiji, disclosed that the transition committee is made up of seasoned technocrats, present and former public office holders and experts from diverse fields of endeavour, including the academics, the media and others. According to the statement, the committee will be inaugurated by Adeleke tomorrow.